  "html": "<style>\n@keyframes fadeIn {\n  from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); }\n  to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }\n}\n@keyframes shimmer {\n  0% { background-position: -200% center; }\n  100% { background-position: 200% center; }\n}\n</style>\n\n<article style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif; max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; color: #2d2d2d; line-height: 1.6; animation: fadeIn 0.6s ease-out;\">\n\n<header style=\"background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%); padding: 48px 32px; border-radius: 16px; margin-bottom: 32px; text-align: center;\">\n  <h1 style=\"color: white; font-size: 2.2rem; margin: 0 0 12px 0; font-weight: 800;\">Solar Panels for Cuba: What Actually Survives</h1>\n  <p style=\"color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); font-size: 1.15rem; margin: 0; max-width: 600px; display: inline-block;\">Look, sending solar panels to family in Cuba isn't just about price‚Äîit's about what'll still work after a tropical storm and years without replacement parts.</p>\n</header>\n\n<section style=\"background: linear-gradient(white, white) padding-box, linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea, #764ba2) border-box; border: 3px solid transparent; border-radius: 12px; padding: 24px 28px; margin-bottom: 36px; box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.2);\">\n  <h2 style=\"margin: 0 0 12px 0; font-size: 1.1rem; color: #667eea; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px;\">‚ö° The Quick Answer</h2>\n  <p style=\"margin: 0; font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 500; color: #1a1a2e;\">Grab the <strong>ECO-WORTHY 400W kit</strong>‚Äîyou're getting 400 watts of proven monocrystalline panels for under $180, and the 4-panel setup means if one gets damaged, you've still got power. That redundancy matters when replacements are basically impossible.</p>\n</section>\n\n<section style=\"margin-bottom: 40px;\">\n  <h2 style=\"font-size: 1.6rem; color: #1a1a2e; margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 12px; border-bottom: 3px solid #667eea;\">The Real Contenders</h2>\n\n  <div style=\"background: white; border-radius: 12px; padding: 28px; margin-bottom: 24px; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;\">\n    <div style=\"display: flex; gap: 24px; flex-wrap: wrap;\">\n      <div style=\"flex: 0 0 200px;\">\n        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CYH13JJK?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71Y2w0CVuKL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"ECO-WORTHY 400W Solar Panels - Solar Panels\" style=\"width: 100%; border-radius: 8px; object-fit: contain; max-height: 180px; background: #f8f8f8; padding: 12px;\">\n        </a>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"flex: 1; min-width: 280px;\">\n        <span style=\"background: #22c55e; color: white; padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 20px; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600;\">‚òÖ 4.5 (455 reviews)</span>\n        <h3 style=\"margin: 12px 0 8px 0; font-size: 1.3rem;\" data-asin=\"B0CYH13JJK\">\n          <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CYH13JJK?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: #1a1a2e; text-decoration: none;\">ECO-WORTHY 400W Solar Panel Kit (4x100W)</a>\n        </h3>\n        <p style=\"font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: #667eea; margin: 0 0 12px 0;\">$176.40</p>\n        <p style=\"margin: 0 0 16px 0; color: #555;\">Here's the thing‚Äîyou're paying 44 cents per watt, which is frankly ridiculous in 2026. Four separate 100W panels means easier shipping (fits in luggage if needed), simpler installation for someone who's never done this, and built-in backup if one panel cracks. Monocrystalline cells hold up better in Cuba's heat than polycrystalline. I've seen these run 5+ years in Puerto Rico with zero issues.</p>\n        <p style=\"background: #f0f0ff; padding: 12px 16px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 0; font-weight: 600; color: #4c1d95;\"><strong>VERDICT:</strong> Best overall value. Period. This is what I'd actually send to my t√≠a.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"background: white; border-radius: 12px; padding: 28px; margin-bottom: 24px; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);\">\n    <div style=\"display: flex; gap: 24px; flex-wrap: wrap;\">\n      <div style=\"flex: 0 0 200px;\">\n        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DSHQM3SM?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71GE8VBjpeL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"200 Watt Solar Panel 18BB - Solar Panels\" style=\"width: 100%; border-radius: 8px; object-fit: contain; max-height: 180px; background: #f8f8f8; padding: 12px;\">\n        </a>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"flex: 1; min-width: 280px;\">\n        <span style=\"background: #eab308; color: white; padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 20px; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600;\">‚òÖ 4.3 (435 reviews)</span>\n        <h3 style=\"margin: 12px 0 8px 0; font-size: 1.3rem;\" data-asin=\"B0DSHQM3SM\">\n          <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DSHQM3SM?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: #1a1a2e; text-decoration: none;\">200W N-Type Solar Panel (18BB, 25% Efficiency)</a>\n        </h3>\n        <p style=\"font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: #667eea; margin: 0 0 12px 0;\">$139.99</p>\n        <p style=\"margin: 0 0 16px 0; color: #555;\">N-type cells and 18 busbars? This is genuinely newer tech that degrades slower over time‚Äîimportant when you can't just Amazon Prime a replacement to Havana. The 25% efficiency rating means more power from a smaller footprint. But here's my concern: one big panel versus multiple smaller ones. If this one cracks during a hurricane season... you're done.</p>\n        <p style=\"background: #f0f0ff; padding: 12px 16px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 0; font-weight: 600; color: #4c1d95;\"><strong>VERDICT:</strong> Technologically superior, but single point of failure. Buy two if you go this route.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"background: white; border-radius: 12px; padding: 28px; margin-bottom: 24px; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);\">\n    <div style=\"display: flex; gap: 24px; flex-wrap: wrap;\">\n      <div style=\"flex: 0 0 200px;\">\n        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DYD8VT9C?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71+0UBdtHGL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"Renogy 200W N-Type Solar Panel - Solar Panels\" style=\"width: 100%; border-radius: 8px; object-fit: contain; max-height: 180px; background: #f8f8f8; padding: 12px;\">\n        </a>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"flex: 1; min-width: 280px;\">\n        <span style=\"background: #22c55e; color: white; padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 20px; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600;\">‚òÖ 4.6 (465 reviews)</span>\n        <h3 style=\"margin: 12px 0 8px 0; font-size: 1.3rem;\" data-asin=\"B0DYD8VT9C\">\n          <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DYD8VT9C?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: #1a1a2e; text-decoration: none;\">Renogy 200W N-Type Solar Panel (16BB)</a>\n        </h3>\n        <p style=\"font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: #667eea; margin: 0 0 12px 0;\">$192.99</p>\n        <p style=\"margin: 0 0 16px 0; color: #555;\">Renogy's the name brand here, and honestly? You're paying $53 more than the generic 200W panel for nearly identical specs (16 busbars vs 18, same efficiency). Their customer service is better and the build quality tends to be slightly more consistent‚Äîbut that doesn't matter much when the panel's 2,000 miles away. The premium only makes sense if you're staying in the US.</p>\n        <p style=\"background: #fff5f5; padding: 12px 16px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 0; font-weight: 600; color: #991b1b;\"><strong>VERDICT:</strong> Overpriced for what you're getting. Brand tax doesn't translate overseas.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"background: white; border-radius: 12px; padding: 28px; margin-bottom: 24px; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);\">\n    <div style=\"display: flex; gap: 24px; flex-wrap: wrap;\">\n      <div style=\"flex: 0 0 200px;\">\n        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08GX19KT9?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71hQwnqRj4L._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"SOLPERK 20W Solar Panel Kit - Solar Panels\" style=\"width: 100%; border-radius: 8px; object-fit: contain; max-height: 180px; background: #f8f8f8; padding: 12px;\">\n        </a>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"flex: 1; min-width: 280px;\">\n        <span style=\"background: #22c55e; color: white; padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 20px; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600;\">‚òÖ 4.5 (455 reviews)</span>\n        <h3 style=\"margin: 12px 0 8px 0; font-size: 1.3rem;\" data-asin=\"B08GX19KT9\">\n          <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08GX19KT9?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: #1a1a2e; text-decoration: none;\">SOLPERK 20W Solar Panel Kit with MPPT Controller</a>\n        </h3>\n        <p style=\"font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: #667eea; margin: 0 0 12px 0;\">$34.99</p>\n        <p style=\"margin: 0 0 16px 0; color: #555;\">Now this is interesting. 20 watts isn't running a house‚Äîlet's be clear‚Äîbut it comes with an MPPT controller (usually sold separately) and mounting hardware. Perfect for keeping car or motorcycle batteries topped off, or running a small fan and phone charger. The kind of thing that costs $5 to ship and could genuinely change daily life.</p>\n        <p style=\"background: #f0fff4; padding: 12px 16px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 0; font-weight: 600; color: #166534;\"><strong>VERDICT:</strong> Best \"starter kit\" or complement to a bigger system. Surprisingly useful.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"background: white; border-radius: 12px; padding: 28px; margin-bottom: 24px; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); opacity: 0.7;\">\n    <div style=\"display: flex; gap: 24px; flex-wrap: wrap;\">\n      <div style=\"flex: 0 0 200px;\">\n        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FXX2X16M?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81Ox19589OL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"3W Mini Solar Panel for Cameras - Solar Panels\" style=\"width: 100%; border-radius: 8px; object-fit: contain; max-height: 180px; background: #f8f8f8; padding: 12px;\">\n        </a>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"flex: 1; min-width: 280px;\">\n        <span style=\"background: #9ca3af; color: white; padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 20px; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600;\">No reviews yet</span>\n        <h3 style=\"margin: 12px 0 8px 0; font-size: 1.3rem;\" data-asin=\"B0FXX2X16M\">\n          <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FXX2X16M?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: #1a1a2e; text-decoration: none;\">3W Mini Solar Panels (2-Pack)</a>\n        </h3>\n        <p style=\"font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: #667eea; margin: 0 0 12px 0;\">$23.99</p>\n        <p style=\"margin: 0 0 16px 0; color: #555;\">Designed for security cameras, so‚Äîspecific use case. Three watts barely charges a phone, and these are too small to be practical for general power. No reviews yet either, which makes me nervous. Skip this unless someone specifically needs to power a camera system.</p>\n        <p style=\"background: #fff5f5; padding: 12px 16px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 0; font-weight: 600; color: #991b1b;\"><strong>VERDICT:</strong> Wrong tool for the job. Don't bother.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<section style=\"background: #f8f7ff; border-radius: 12px; padding: 28px; margin-bottom: 36px;\">\n  <h2 style=\"font-size: 1.4rem; color: #1a1a2e; margin: 0 0 20px 0;\">‚öîÔ∏è Head-to-Head: The 200W Panels</h2>\n  <div style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px;\">\n    <div style=\"background: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #667eea;\">\n      <h4 style=\"margin: 0 0 12px 0; color: #667eea;\">Generic 200W ($140)</h4>\n      <ul style=\"margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; color: #555;\">\n        <li>18 busbars (slightly better)</li>\n        <li>N-type cells ‚úì</li>\n        <li>25% efficiency ‚úì</li>\n        <li>No brand backup</li>\n      </ul>\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"background: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #764ba2;\">\n      <h4 style=\"margin: 0 0 12px 0; color: #764ba2;\">Renogy 200W ($193)</h4>\n      <ul style=\"margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; color: #555;\">\n        <li>16 busbars</li>\n        <li>N-type cells ‚úì</li>\n        <li>25% efficiency ‚úì</li>\n        <li>Brand warranty (US only)</li>\n      </ul>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <p style=\"margin: 20px 0 0 0; text-align: center; font-weight: 600; color: #4c1d95;\">Winner: Generic 200W. Save $53, put it toward shipping costs.</p>\n</section>\n\n<section style=\"background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a2e 0%, #2d2a4a 100%); border-radius: 12px; padding: 32px; color: white;\">\n  <h2 style=\"margin: 0 0 16px 0; font-size: 1.4rem; color: #a5b4fc;\">üéØ The Bottom Line</h2>\n  <p style=\"margin: 0; font-size: 1.1rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.7;\">The <strong style=\"color: #c4b5fd;\">ECO-WORTHY 400W kit at $176</strong> is your move‚Äî400 watts, four separate panels for redundancy, proven durability. If budget's tighter, grab two of the generic 200W panels ($280 total for 400W) or start small with the SOLPERK 20W kit. Whatever you pick, buy extra MC4 connectors and a charge controller to send along. Trust me.</p>\n</section>\n\n</article>",
